snippet.textDisplay:
ACTION!
Can't relate to most of this...
Except the hair problems. My hair would get stuck in chairs, seatbelts, doors, zipped up in my jacket, in my bookbag, It would always be tangled, would take forever to wash and it would clog the drain... It got so unmanageable for me I kept in in a braid 90% of the time ponytail the other 10%. Then they would get in the way too! So I know the struggle.
For all of these reasons (and more), I didn't see the point of long hair that I didn't use that was always in the way.
So I got it chopped off. I now have a pixie cut, super cute, and I don't have to worry about any of this stuff. Short hair isn't for everyone, but if your living with these daily struggles and don't "use/ style" your hair, this may be an alternative you never considered 😉. I recommend looking into it. Heck I did and now I'm realizing I should've done it sooner.
And CUT! (Lol had to)
